<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><!--Arbortext, Inc., 1988-2018, v.4002--><description xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" appl="X07|X82|X91|XFB|XFC|XFD|XFE|XZH|XZG|XZJ|XJA|XJE|XJB|XFK|XBB|XJL|XHN|XCB|XBC|X38|X35|XBG|X33|XBA|XFA|X74|X73|X76|XJK|X75|X70|XJD|XJC|XFF|XJH|X77|XJF|X79|X27|X29|XTP|X24|X65|X64|X63|X62|X61|X67|X66|X57|X58|X55|X56|XDD|X10|X59|X53|X54|X17|X52|X90|X92|X09|X95|XHA|X98|X44|X45|XRQ|X47|X48|XEF|X40|X41|X42|X43|X06|X83|X81|X87|X85|X84|XJ1|XDE|X1310|XR210|X1316|X1317|XR310|X1322|X1318|XZ110|X1312" id="RDE-000323804" xml:lang="en" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:ptc:names:renault:dita:xsd:description.xsd"><title translate="no">laser welding without filler metal : description</title><descprolog translate="no"><status name="Published" translate="no"/><critdates translate="no"><created date="03/11/21 08:25" translate="no"/><revised modified="10/10/24 13:47" translate="no"/></critdates><descmetadata translate="no"><siename translate="no">laser welding without filler metal : description</siename><sieversion translate="no">F.1</sieversion><sietype translate="yes">Description</sietype><sienumber translate="no">RDE-000323804</sienumber><domain translate="no">MR</domain><company translate="no">RENAULT</company></descmetadata></descprolog><descbody translate="no"><descsection translate="no"><figure id="fig1" translate="no"><title translate="yes">EXAMPLE: ROOF</title><image dimension="F1 (85x60) #" href="../MergedPictures/ILL-000026490.PNG" style="width: 85.0mm; height: 60.0mm;" translate="no"/><illusnum>RDE-000323804-01-000026490</illusnum></figure></descsection></descbody><description id="des1" translate="no"><title translate="yes">DISASSEMBLY</title><description id="des2" translate="no"><title translate="yes">CUTTING</title><descbody translate="no"><descsection translate="no"><figure id="fig2" translate="no"><image dimension="F1 (85x60) #" href="../MergedPictures/ILL-000026492.PNG" style="width: 85.0mm; height: 60.0mm;" translate="no"/><illusnum>RDE-000323804-02-000026492</illusnum></figure><para id="par1" translate="yes">Cut the part around each laser bead <sieref href="x-wc://gie=OR:wt.part.WTPartMaster:3504226"><linkdesc>body structure cutting tools : description</linkdesc><linkvalue>GIEMR-001619</linkvalue></sieref>.</para><para id="par2" translate="yes">Remove the damaged part.</para></descsection></descbody></description><description id="des3" translate="no"><title translate="yes">GRINDING</title><descbody translate="no"><descsection translate="no"><marklayer translate="no"><mark id="e53e365c-15ca-446d-816c-7fcbf1c4c81e" translate="no"><mcomponent translate="no"><label translate="no"/></mcomponent><designation translate="no">1</designation></mark></marklayer><figure id="fig3" translate="no"><image dimension="F1 (85x60) #" href="../MergedPictures/ILL-000026494_lay-000318565.png" style="width: 85.0mm; height: 60.0mm;" translate="no"/><illusnum>RDE-000323804-03-000026494</illusnum></figure><para id="par3" translate="yes">Level off the tabs <markref format="dita" href="#des3/fig3" scope="local" translate="no" type="figure">1</markref> remaining on the vehicle using an orbital sander fitted with a flap disc <sieref href="x-wc://gie=OR:wt.part.WTPartMaster:3469218"><linkdesc>shaving tools : description</linkdesc><linkvalue>GIEMR-001611</linkvalue></sieref>.</para></descsection></descbody></description></description><description id="des4" translate="no"><title translate="yes">PREPARATION BEFORE ASSEMBLY</title><description id="des5" translate="no"><title translate="yes">POSITIONING AND ADJUSTMENT</title><descbody translate="no"><para id="par4" translate="yes">Position the replacement part, adjust it and fix it using the locking pliers <sieref href="x-wc://gie=OR:wt.part.WTPartMaster:3503961"><linkdesc>body structure maintenance and adjustment tools : use</linkdesc><linkvalue>GIEMR-001610</linkvalue></sieref>.</para><para id="par5" translate="yes">If necessary, reassemble the adjacent components and check the panel gaps.</para></descbody></description><description id="des6" translate="no"><title translate="yes">MARKING AND IDENTIFYING THE JOINTS</title><descbody translate="no"><descsection translate="no"><para id="par6" translate="yes">Mark its optimum position using masking tape between the replacement part and the vehicle.</para><para id="par7" translate="yes">Remove the replacement part.</para></descsection></descbody></description><description id="des7" translate="no"><title translate="yes">PREPARING THE MATING FACES ON THE REPLACEMENT PART</title><descbody translate="no"><para id="par8" translate="yes">Lightly sand the internal mating faces of the replacement part at the bonding zones using <technicalvalue translate="no"><value translate="yes">P320</value></technicalvalue> dry sand paper or a red abrasive pad without removing the protection.</para><para id="par9" translate="yes">Prepare the rest of the replacement part according to the joint type.</para></descbody></description><description id="des8" translate="no"><title translate="yes">PREPARATION OF THE MATING FACES ON THE VEHICLE</title><descbody translate="no"><para id="par10" translate="yes">Lightly sand the internal mating faces at the bonding zones using <technicalvalue translate="no"><value translate="yes">P320</value></technicalvalue> dry sand paper or a red abrasive pad without removing the protection.</para><para id="par11" translate="yes">Prepare the rest of the vehicle according to the joint type.</para></descbody></description><description id="des9" translate="no"><title translate="yes">APPLY THE PROTECTION BEFORE ASSEMBLY</title><descbody translate="no"><para id="par12" translate="yes"><sieref href="x-wc://gie=OR:wt.part.WTPartMaster:3465485"><linkdesc>anti-corrosion protection before assembly : description</linkdesc><linkvalue>GIEMR-001838</linkvalue></sieref>.</para></descbody></description></description><description id="des10" translate="no"><title translate="yes">ASSEMBLY</title><description id="des11" translate="no"><title translate="yes">APPLICATION OF THE BONDING PRODUCTS</title><descbody translate="no"><para translate="yes">Degrease the bonding zones on the replacement part and the vehicle using heptane.</para><para id="par13" translate="yes">Apply a structural cement bead over the whole internal mating face of the vehicle <sieref href="x-wc://gie=OR:wt.part.WTPartMaster:3485957"><linkdesc>body structure bonding with hard mastic : description</linkdesc><linkvalue>GIEMR-000171</linkvalue></sieref>.</para></descbody></description><description id="des12" translate="no"><title translate="yes">FITTING AND ADJUSTING THE REPLACED PARTS</title><descbody translate="no"><descsection translate="no"><figure id="fig4" translate="no"><image dimension="F1 (85x60) #" href="../MergedPictures/ILL-000026491.PNG" style="width: 85.0mm; height: 60.0mm;" translate="no"/><illusnum>RDE-000323804-04-000026491</illusnum><?Pub Caret -1?></figure><para id="par14" translate="yes">Position the replacement part on the vehicle.</para><para id="par15" translate="yes">Hold the replacement part with the locking pliers to position it securely according to the marks made earlier <sieref href="x-wc://gie=OR:wt.part.WTPartMaster:3503961"><linkdesc>body structure maintenance and adjustment tools : use</linkdesc><linkvalue>GIEMR-001610</linkvalue></sieref>.</para></descsection><para id="par16" translate="yes">Comb up the surplus bonding before it dries.</para></descbody></description><description id="des13" translate="no"><title translate="yes">MAKING THE OTHER JOINTS</title><descbody translate="no"><descsection translate="no"><para id="par17" translate="yes">Make the rest of the replacement part joints.</para></descsection></descbody></description><description id="des14" translate="no"><title translate="yes">FINISHING AND SHAPING</title><descbody translate="no"><descsection translate="no"><para id="par18" translate="yes"><sieref href="x-wc://gie=OR:wt.part.WTPartMaster:3533817"><linkdesc>bodywork component straightening : description</linkdesc><linkvalue>GIEMR-001887</linkvalue></sieref>.</para></descsection></descbody></description></description></description>